<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="367" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="12.[140,1108,1293,1460]" pageId="12" pageNumber="367">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[140,325,1293,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Gyrinidae" genus="Gyrinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventralis">
<emphasis box="[140,325,1293,1320]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="367">Gyrinus ventralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[549,730,1293,1320]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="12" pageNumber="367">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roughley RE" box="[772,968,1293,1319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="367" pagination="72 - 673" refId="ref7727" refString="Roughley RE (1991) Family Gyrinidae: Whirligig Beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Ottawa, Ontario: Agriculture Canada, publication 1861 / E: pp. 72 - 673. http: // www. canacoll. org / Coleo / Checklist / PDF files / GYRINIDAE. pdf [accessed 29 June 2009]" type="journal article" year="1991">Roughley (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Morrissette R" pageId="12" pageNumber="367" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref7605" refString="Morrissette R (1979) Les coleopteres Gyrinidae du Quebec. Cordulia, Supplement 8: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1979">Morrissette (1979)</bibRefCitation>
reported that it prefers fluvial lakes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Oygur S &amp; Wolfe GW" box="[641,928,1328,1354]" pageId="12" pageNumber="367" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref7625" refString="Oygur S, Wolfe GW (1991) Classification, distribution and phylogeny of North American (north of Mexico) species of Gyrinus Muller (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 207: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Oygur and Wolfe (1991)</bibRefCitation>
reported it primarily (80%) from lentic habitats. We have not been able to find voucher specimens of this species from 
<collectingRegion box="[360,540,1399,1425]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="12" pageNumber="367">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
in any Canadian collection. Consequently, further research should be conducted to ascertain if this species actually occurs in the province.
</paragraph>
